609 A.2d 1192 ATTORNEY GRIEVANCE COMMISSION OF MARYLAND v. Guillermo Rafael DIAZ-FONTANA a/k/a William R. Diaz-Fontana. Misc. (Subtitle BV) No. 20,

Sept. Term, 1992.

Court of Appeals of Maryland. Aug. 12, 1992.

ORDER

Upon consideration of the consent to disbarment from the practice of law filed by Guillermo Rafael Diaz-Fontana in accordance with Maryland Rule BV12 d 2, and. the written recommendation of Bar Counsel, it is this 12th day of August 1992

ORDERED, by the Court of Appeals of Maryland, that Guillermo Rafael Diaz-Fontana be, and he is hereby, disbarred by consent from the further practice of law in the State of Maryland; and it is further

ORDERED that the Clerk of this Court shall strike the name of Guillermo Rafael Diaz-Fontana from the register of attorneys, and pursuant to Maryland Rule BV13, shall certify that fact to the Trustees of the Clients’ Security Trust Fund and the clerks of all judicial tribunals in the State.
